  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2020",
  "title": "react-router v4 example outdated",
  "body": "Code Reference: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/tree/v2/packages/react-instantsearch/examples/react-router-v4\r\n\r\nLooks like this implementation is based in a old react-router v4 proposition.\r\n\r\nNew version is under `react-router-dom@next`, more info here: https://reacttraining.com/react-router.\r\n\r\nI tried to update and make a PR but my code doesn't work ¯\\_(ツ)_/¯\r\n\r\nIn particular under `onSearchStateChange` the API is slightly different:\r\n\r\n- `const {router} = this.context` is missing. maybe `this.props`?\r\n- `.replaceWith` and `.transitionTo` not  #exists. maybe `.replace` and `.push`?\r\n\r\n\r\nI think the old `context` object is now `this.props`: https://reacttraining.com/react-router/#contexthistory",
